snippet.textDisplay:
I'd have to disagree with the RE comment. I had this amazing teacher for it when I went to secondary school in England. It was half of the years' favorite subject. We'd have class discussions and debates, and for many of us, it was our first proper exposure to intense topics such as abortion and euthanasia.

Our teacher always played Socrates, questioning us. In a way it was kind of like a pre-philosophy class where we learnt about religions as well as different social issues, and were able to explore them in an accepting environment. I have a lot of good memories of that class - RE teachers do good work.
